The crash on Monday morning brings the road death toll for the Western Cape to at least 17 since Friday. CAPE TOWN Four people have been killed and six others have been seriously injured in a collision between two taxis and a car between Beaufort West and Aberdeen.The crash this morning brings the road death toll for the Western Cape to at least 17 since Friday.Western Cape Traffic Chief Kenny Africa says, The situation on the Aberdeen Road is four dead, six seriously injured and the medical rescue personnel are at the scene of the accident and the road is currently closed for traffic. 